<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Learn DSA</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <%- include('../../partials/head') %>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="d-flex">
      <%- include('../../partials/sidebar') %>

      <main class="flex-fill p-4">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h3>Pre-Order Traversal</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Pre-Order Traversal: Introduction

            Pre-order traversal is a way to visit all nodes in a tree.

            It follows a specific order:
            1. Visit the root
            2. Traverse the left subtree
            3. Traverse the right subtree

            ####Order = Root → Left → Right####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[Root]-->B[Left];
              A-->C[Right];
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Step-by-Step Process

            At each node:
            - First, process the current node
            - Then recursively traverse the left child
            - Finally traverse the right child

            This is a **depth-first traversal** strategy.

            ####PreOrder(T) = visit(T) + PreOrder(T.left) + PreOrder(T.right)####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A-->B;
              A-->C;
              B-->D;
              B-->E;
              C-->F;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Example Traversal

            Given the tree:

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[1]-->B[2];
              A-->C[3];
              B-->D[4];
              B-->E[5];
            /mermaid

            Pre-order traversal result:

            ####1 → 2 → 4 → 5 → 3####

            Steps:
            - Visit 1
            - Go left (2 → 4 → 5)
            - Then right (3)
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Recursive Implementation

            Pre-order is naturally implemented using recursion.

            Pseudo-code:

            ####
            PreOrder(node):
              if node == null:
                return
              visit(node)
              PreOrder(node.left)
              PreOrder(node.right)
            ####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[Call]-->B[Visit Node];
              B-->C[Left Subtree];
              C-->D[Right Subtree];
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Iterative Approach (Stack)

            We can also implement pre-order traversal using a stack.

            Steps:
            1. Push root onto stack
            2. Pop node and visit it
            3. Push right child
            4. Push left child

            (Stack ensures left is processed first)

            ####Time = O(n), Space = O(n)####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[Stack]-->B[Push Root];
              B-->C[Pop + Visit];
              C-->D[Push Right];
              D-->E[Push Left];
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <!-- CONTROLS --> 
        <div class="nav-controls"> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark me-2" id="prev">← Prev</button> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark" id="next">Next →</button> 
        </div> 
        <div class="progress-container"> 
          <div class="progress-bar" id="progress"></div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide-counter"> 
          <span id="current">1</span>/<span id="total">1</span> 
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
  <script src="/javascripts/render-slides.js"></script>
</html>
